                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–1747: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-17T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 17, 1947—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 17—4:12
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2408. Carson Chang left Shanghai Dec. 13 by air for US. Reliable American
                    controlled source close Chang states Chang’s only purpose present visit is
                    attempt interview Secretary State and George Kennan<note n="91" xml:id="d312fn1"
                        >Director of Policy Planning Staff.</note> and that he is using University
                    Washington lectureship as blind. Source further states Chang asserts to Chinese
                    friends only posts he would accept in Chinese Govt are President or
                    Vice-President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
